cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with a problem in geometric settings and involves finding subsets of geometric shapes that cover a set of points. This is a classic problem in computational geometry and hence, cs.CG is the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes algorithms for solving the set multi-cover problem and discusses their approximation ratios. This makes cs.DS a likely sub-category as well.
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The set multi-cover problem is a combinatorial optimization problem and involves finding a minimum cardinality subset of sets that satisfy certain requirements. This makes cs.DM a possible sub-category.
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the approximation ratio for the set multi-cover problem and involves game-theoretic concepts such as VC-dimension. This makes cs.GT a possible sub-category.
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of the set multi-cover problem and proposes algorithms with approximation ratios. This makes cs.CC a possible sub-category as well.
